# Format: CVE-YYYY-XXXXX [exp:YYYY-MM-DD] followed by comment with justification

# =============================================================================
# INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# Add CVEs below with clear justification for why they are being ignored.
# 
# Format Options:
#   CVE-YYYY-XXXXX                    # Ignore permanently
#   CVE-YYYY-XXXXX exp:2025-12-31    # Ignore until expiration date
#
# Valid reasons include:
# - False positive (CVE doesn't affect our usage)
# - No fix available yet (with plan to revisit)
# - Accepted risk (with business approval)
# - Applies to dev dependencies only (not in production)
# - Vulnerability in transitive dependency with no direct fix
#
# Example entries:
# CVE-2023-12345 exp:2025-06-30
# Justification: False positive - vulnerability in unused module path
#
# CVE-2023-67890 exp:2025-03-31
# Justification: No fix available - monitoring upstream for patch
